    "description": "These data contain down-welled global shortwave hemispherical radiation taken during the Wisconsin FIRE/SRB experiment. The data set consists of measurement\\ s taken every minute for 17 ground stations during the daylight hours. The data include values from October 12 through November 2, 1986.The number, location, latitude, and longitude of the FIRE/SRB WISCONSIN sites are: NUMBER LOCATION LATITUDE(DEG N) LONGITUDE(DEG W) 1 FT. MCCOY 43.96 90.76 2 STEVENS POINT 44.55 89.53 3 BARABOO 43.52 89.77 4 ADAMS COUNTY 43.97 89.80 5 WAUTOMA 44.04 89.30 6 WAUSAU 44.92 89.62 7 ARLINGTON 43.33 89.37 8 PORTAGE 43.56 89.48 9 REEDSBURG 43.53 89.97 10 PLAIN 43.28 90.04 11 TRI-COUNTY 43.21 90.19 12 DODGEVILLE 42.99 90.15 13 MT. HOREB 43.00 89.74 14 ARENA 43.16 89.91 15 SAUK CITY 43.30 89.74 16 MIDDLETON 43.11 89.53 17 MADISON 43.13 89.32",
